Flittum.Desc: It's thought to be one of the smallest species of Doodles in the world. Flittum are incredibly agile in flight, and feed on the juices they can suck from fruit and nectar from flowers.

Drakothread.Desc: It doesn't need food in order to survive. Despite its size, it yearns for comfort and reassurance, and for someone to love it.

Skorpent.Desc: Sly and sneaky, Skorpent will go out of their way to steal food or belongings from smaller, weaker, or oblivious people or Doodles, rather than getting their own.

Partybug.Desc: Partybug spend the majority of their lives learning how to do basic party tricks and simple magic. They are so dedicated to their craft, that their donning of wizard clothing became an evolutionary trait.

Furzen.Desc: Furzen have thick, fluffy fur. Sadly, it is freezing to the touch. Large patches of frost, even during the summer, can suggest that a pack has recently come through.

Candeigon.Desc: Candeigon are highly intelligent. It's often ambitious, and if it so chooses, can utilize or abuse its psychic abilities to force its will on others. When angered, the various spots of candy on its body will grow into sharp points in a threatening display.

Cacmeow.Desc: Cacmeow are friendly and cuddly. Due to its spiny body, it has difficulty making friends. Those who give it a chance, however, know it to be among the most loyal of companions.

Bunsweet.Desc: It has a distinct sweet smell. Bunsweet enjoy playtime with children and sharing the sweet, edible fluff at the tips of its ears.

Jelluminous.Desc: Jelluminous uses its glowing head to its advantage, and uses its lampshade to cover the light it emits when necessary. This blinking motion attracts many smaller Doodles, and they are thus turned into food.

Agotoad.Desc: When preparing an attack, the pouches on its cheeks swell with flames. Then, it expels it in a fiery burst.

Zapoeira.Desc: It often prefers to keep its eyes closed, instead reading the unique bioelectrical currents of the world around it to navigate. It fights with a unique style of kicks.

Klicki.Desc: It taps its wings together to create an iconic clicking sound, similar to that of a computer mouse. It uses these sounds to communicate with other Klicki. Scientists have found that the way in which they communicate is similar to binary.

Incinelisk.Desc: Despite their frightening appearance, Incinelisk are protective and doting parents - but beware, as they are violently territorial and defensive over their young. Once two become mates, they are bonded for life.

Somberock.Desc: It's calm and peaceful, even in the face of death. It makes the most of the present, and the friends that it has. Sometimes, in spite of its happiness, it will look sad.

Blossafaun.Desc: A Blossafaun attracts others of its own by spinning around in a unique dance, releasing a smell that only it can detect. It hides from threats by jumping into water or nearby cracks and crevices.

Gowatt.Desc: The jagged horns of a Gowatt are capable of conducting strikes of electricity, which it then stores for later use. As such, they are valuable on the market.

Bengalux.Desc: Bengalux is hyper-aware of others due to its increased powers, generally on edge to the world around it. It's often extremely judgmental based on what it senses.

Snortles.Desc: Snortles are shy and withdrawn. They spend their days foraging for plants and berries, seeking to nurture the tree sprout that serves as their tail.

Theaterror.Desc: It weeps constantly, spreading misery wherever it goes. It seems to refuse to let itself feel joy.

Voltatoo.Desc: Voltatoo are well known for their chatty, loud voices, as well as their friendly and energetic demeanors. They have a tendency to shock their tamers when they become too excited.

Glubbie.Desc: This strange creature came from an alternate universe. It seems like its main purpose coming here was to have fun! It particularly likes to pull pranks.

Appluff.Desc: Appluff live in massive flocks, all preferring to perch on the same tree or fly in swarms. Their bright red coloration makes them easy to spot from a distance.

Polargeist.Desc: Polargeist prefers to inhabit the bodies of the recently deceased. Very few have seen its true form and lived to tell about it. They are aggressive and unpredictable. Should you spot one, run.

Henchum.Desc: Henchum are Riffrats who realized that they have no aptitude for stealing. Instead, they use their brute strength to force others to comply.

Malotrick.Desc: It hides inside of chests and lures trainers to open the chest using its psychic powers. Once the chest is opened, it hypnotizes the trainer and steals their money to add to its hoard of treasure.

Octonut.Desc: Due to its lack of a skeleton, it's capable of squeezing itself into tiny holes, however, as it refuses to part with the coconut on its head, it doesn't. Octonut are known to make poor decisions frequently.

Squed.Desc: Squed is a lonely doodle, often avoided by almost every other, including themselves. It is probably because of their huge forehead which is intimidating to most other Doodles.

Ruffire.Desc: When angered, its thick and fluffy fur flares up with flames. It takes advantage of this to intimidate and harm larger foes. It rarely backs down from a fight.

Grufflin.Desc: It has a piercing, screeching cry. A Grufflin's bright red feathers are often collected and sold. When cleaned, they are a popular decorative addition to fruity drinks, as they add the faint taste of apple.

Faunsprout.Desc: It seems to never run out of energy. It's nearly always in motion, following the sun and only stopping to rest when the moon rises.

Maelzuri.Desc: Maelzuri are extremely rare, and sightings are few and far inbetween. Some believe it doesn't exist at all. Those who have met this Doodle describe it as gentle and curious, and mention that it seemed to enjoy rifling through belongings.

Magmotode.Desc: It can refine raw ores into molten metals using its specialized, super-heated arms. In defense, it sprays the molten liquid or steam at its foes to ward them away.

Megortles.Desc: Some Megortles have been known to live for much longer than a century. They live deep in the forests, among the ancient trees and plants, nurturing the tree sprout that serves as their tail. When they finally pass, it will grow into a magnificent tree.

Noxvul.Desc: The result of a Flaskit that was exposed to a reactive catalyst. Its gaseous body is highly toxic, and it uses this to its advantage.

Horbeast.Desc: It uses its powerful arms and grip to pull branches from trees when making shelters. It will occasionally use these shelters to lure in prey, hiding and waiting in the shadows.

Boulduo.Desc: Although they have two heads and brains, Boulduo are not very intelligent. Formed by fused Pebblett, their new body is clumsy and top-heavy.

Maskrow.Desc: The mask in which it wears doesn't come off. It is said that if you were to view a Maskrow's true face, it would send your soul to the void.

Tabbolt.Desc: It rarely opens its eyes, even when awake. Tabbolt frequently takes naps to manage its unstable electricity. It's prone to electrical discharge without warning.

Xenoxious.Desc: Xenoxious has an insatiable urge for combat, frequently instigating fights both between other Doodles to watch or itself. It is very impatient.

Gigarlic.Desc: It typically prefers to lounge in one place, only getting up to satiate its ravenous appetite. Its internal temperature is hot enough to boil water.

Spectatik.Desc: It has a swagger to its step, and radiates coolness. The crystalline shades that adorn its face only add to that fact. It seems to not have a care in the world.

Kelpimer.Desc: It takes advantage of the weak or confused, luring its victims to the edge of the water before dragging them under. It prefers to stay in dark or murky waters.

Clankey.Desc: Always eager to duel. It yearns to hone its skill and strength to protect those it cares about, and to prepare itself for evolution.

Leapo.Desc: It spends its time rummaging about the fallen foliage of the forest floor, blending in and digging up small insects from beneath the leaves.

Mold.Desc: A species related to Moss, now becoming more common in recent years. It frequents sewers and other filthy areas, where the once pure water that made up its body has become tainted and foul.

Pebblett.Desc: Its not quite known how a Pebblett is born. Finding one by its lonesome is extremely rare. They do not survive long on their own.

Spirice.Desc: With its newfound powers of ice, it becomes corrupt. The closer it is to evolving, the more wild and uncontrollable it becomes.

Moss.Desc: It prefers to sunbathe on rocks -- this leads to birds and insects trying to prey upon it, but they get blasted away with water.

Gemin.Desc: Its thick, crystalline shell protects it from many forms of harm. Although often approached by Crystik for help or protection, Gemin will generally elect to ignore them.

Marshore.Desc: Its soft, somewhat plush body is useful for creeping around silently. Although it may startle with its soundless approach, it does not do so out of ill-intent.

Tufflaze.Desc: The burns a Tufflaze can inflict are capable of continuing to burn even after being extinguished. Although well aware of the damage it may cause, it doesn't seem to care. It regularly bursts into flames.

Monolugg.Desc: The powerful jaw of a Monolugg is capable of crushing a car in half. Despite their strength, they are very gentle-mannered.

Twigon.Desc: A small, sentient stuffed animal based on a dragon. It frequently seeks out the attention of anyone willing to give it.

Serrafin.Desc: Its intimidating appearance has given rise to many negative stereotypes about it. Although it may curiously bite things with its powerful steel jaw, it's unlikely to actually harm a human.

Kibara.Desc: It has a powerful protective instinct. Kibara focuses its strengths into its defenses, specializing in powerful shields made of condensed ice and crystal. These shields are rumored to be able to block almost any attack.

Gomutt.Desc: Gomutt lazes around in the depths of the sea with its mouth open. Its diet typically consists of unsuspecting Jelluminous and other small organisms.

Schiwi.Desc: Schiwi often get separated from their mothers at birth. Afraid and confused, they find an abandoned bucket thinking its their mother, refusing to return back to the ocean.

Archuma.Desc: Thought to be some of the oldest Doodles in existence, Archuma tend to carry many ancient treasures presumed to be lost to mankind. They guard them fiercely.

Wvyarn.Desc: It uses the ball of yarn it carries to repair its own injuries. A typical Wvyarn's body is littered with rough stitching and patches.

Bunswirl.Desc: A powerful instinct drives Bunswirl to help anybody in need. This, paired with its gentle temperament and sweet scent, makes it a good aide for nurses and doctors in the medical field.

Beetal.Desc: In moments of extreme joy, Beetal will roll on the ground and make a series of clicking sounds. It enjoys being held, and follows its tamer closely on walks.

Bonikrow.Desc: Upon evolving, Bonikrow searches far and wide for a suitable stick. The stick it eventually selects is as important to it as its life.

Flaskit.Desc: Its insides are naturally reactive, albeit harmless. If pushed over, its round body and tiny legs make it difficult to get back up.

Heatza.Desc: Heat radiates from its body. Oddly enough, its gooey, melty exterior has a difficult time getting dirty. It's naturally cheerful, and gets along well with other Doodles.

Wisp.Desc: It has a calm and nomadic nature, and are often seen drifting around at night. If lost, try to wander away from them, as they frequently linger near the center of forests.

Mourveil.Desc: The sounds and cries it makes are similar to that of a human, leading to many stories and local tales of lost souls weeping over the lives they lost. However, these cries most likely belong to a Mourveil.

Humbiscus.Desc: The special feathers on its wings are soft like a flower's petals. In flight, it's easily recognized by its long, ribbonlike tail. In spite of its beauty, it has a particularly ugly call.

Spirasol.Desc: The result of a Kowosu that has trained to its absolute limit and overcome all hardships. Its effort is rewarded by the blinding speed and power of a Spirasol. The quick movements of its sword look like flashes of light that strike with seemingly perfect precision.

Lumiline.Desc: It takes great pride in the crystals around its body. Lumiline can often be seen strutting in the sunlight, showing off. When it attacks, it glows brightly.

Louis.Desc: Its elusive appearance has garnered the interest of many. Its body seems to be equivalent to that of a balloon, and is prone to floating away.

Endovul.Desc: The result of a Flaskit that was exposed to a reactive solution. It radiates a bone-chilling cold, and is particularly fond of naps.

Riffrat.Desc: Riffrat live in swarms under the command of Henchum. They strive to be skillful thieves, but have a tendency to fall short, "stealing" things like fallen change and loose wrappers to hoard in their nests.

Geckgoo.Desc: The skin of a Geckgoo is slick to the touch. It defends itself by secreting a poison that can cause itchiness and irritation.

Tadappole.Desc: Tadappole likes to swim in shallow waters as soon as it hatches from its apple seed. Waters populated with Tadappole are thought to have the faint taste of apple. They are frequent targets of other Doodles due to their sweet taste and pungent fragrance, and the majority of them do not make it to adulthood.

Cerebopod.Desc: It's notably difficult to anger, and slow to jump to violence, in spite of its expansive psychic ability. As a result, Cerebopod is regarded with respect and typically left alone by other wild Doodles.

Apurrition.Desc: Its powers are somewhat volatile and unpredictable. Strange phenomena have been traced back to Apurrition in the past.

Glowcat.Desc: Glowcat will live in large groups harmoniously, sharing supplies equally and communicating information with the use of their whiskers. It's unknown if they have their own language.

Angerler.Desc: Angerler are always in a bad mood. Wild schools will occasionally take part in bullying and toying with other species of Doodles.

Toxipupa.Desc: Toxipupa rarely moves, biding its time until its evolution. Its hard shell and poison are enough to ward off most predators.

Candygrief.Desc: It's highly loyal to the companion it considers its own. On occasion, a Candygrief will mourn seemingly nothing. It's believed it knows that one day its friend will fade away, and the memories with it.

Wydling.Desc: Wydling tends to frequently appear during the winter season. Their hypnotic song must be combated with one of your own, lest they take all of your possessions.

Moyai.Desc: A tourist spilled his swag on a moyai on the island. This Moyai says thank you!

Statikeet.Desc: A flock of Statikeet are capable of disrupting radio waves and electronics due to their method of communication.

Shmellow.Desc: When raised together in a group, Shmellow will often huddle into a near seamless mass when they sleep. This is both for comfort and defense.

Borbek.Desc: It primarily lives by the water in tropical locations. With the use of its strong beak, it cracks open coconuts and consumes them.

Sharazor.Desc: A Sharazor's streamlined body is built for toughness. It will often approach swimmers and divers out of curiosity. Although it means no harm, this has a tendency to cause a fright.

Frigale.Desc: It inflates the heart-shaped sac on its chest full of air to attract the attention of any that may be watching. In any group, the Frigale with the largest sac is regarded with the most respect. Frigale often have a self-important attitude.

Vixalor.Desc: Vixalor are known as the guardians of the forest. Their fox-fire is said to have the power to heal any illness, or scorch any foe.

Abyssent.Desc: Abyssent make their home in the darkest depths of the water. When two meet, they will circle around each other and make a beautiful light show. The brightest dance decides the winner.

Vipember.Desc: Vipember are hissy and nippy. In the wild, they live in swarms with their siblings. They are notorious for starting bushfires.

Tsumo.Desc: Its control over its flames is unparalleled. Stories tell of how this Doodle once single-handedly ended a famine with its superior and delicious cooking. Some have offered tributes to it, and later speak of how they smelled something delicious coming from the forest.

Voltenchant.Desc: In times of extreme drought, Voltenchant have been known to step in and work together to summon powerful storms, so that the water may return.

Tortles.Desc: The tail of a Tortles is actually a small sprout, which will one day grow into a large tree.

Staligant.Desc: The more even their horns, the more stability they have over their crystal; the source of their psychic energy. Female Stalignant are far more aggressive than their male counterparts, and have far more extensive powers.

Archopos.Desc: An Archopos has become one with the treasure it protects. Should the treasure be threatened, it will respond dangerously.

Metalytra.Desc: When feeling playful, Metalytra will attempt to lift its tamer off the ground and fly with them. If it rubs its wings together, the resulting sound is a melodic hum.

Skrappey.Desc: Skrappey is energetic and curious, often dragging its tamer off the path to explore. It loves to play games!

Terruma.Desc: A Terruma has enough power to crush a large boulder with ease. As a result, they have been utilized to help transport heavy loads for years. When they gallop at top speed, their thunderous footsteps are comparable to an earthquake.

Dramask.Desc: The two that are referred to as Dramask are inseparable, and are said to be two halves of the same conscience. Dramask are often unpredictable and moody.

Pompaboar.Desc: It seems to put little to no effort into taking care of its hair, but manages to keep it stylish anyway. For this reason alone, Pompaboar are idolized by Wiglet.

Daeferno.Desc: Repugnant, with few redeeming qualities and fewer good morals. Daeferno relishes in causing anarchy, strengthening its own power by stealing the life force of other Doodles. Despite this, it seems to have no energy, instead preferring to laze around.

Mawthra.Desc: It utilizes the pattern on its wings to intimidate and ward off foes. Its bite contains a poison that will quickly weaken prey.

Snobat.Desc: Snobat frequent cold areas. They live in groups, and huddle together during especially low temperatures to keep warm with the help of their cotton-like fur. Some have found that they enjoy playing in fresh powdered snow.

Pupskey.Desc: Well known for their loyalty and bravery, Pupskey make for popular companions. Their fur is cool to the touch, and their tongues are even colder!

Borbo.Desc: It has no legs, and is unable to fly. Instead, it uses its wings to propel itself forward in a roll, aided by its round body.

Wiglet.Desc: It dedicates its time to collecting anything it can find to make a wig for itself, as an effort to look cool. It idolizes Pompaboar, and groups of Wiglet can be found catering to one.

Squonk.Desc: In the face of its undesirably ugly appearance, a Squonk weeps. Although it may try to hide itself, to find it, you need only follow its trail of tears.

Eftue.Desc: An Eftue will travel far in search of the perfect stone to call its own, and will guard it ferociously. It infuses this stone with its own power, often comforting itself with the resonating energy.

Clangutang.Desc: The massive blade it carries is astonishingly heavy, but it's capable of swinging it around without issue. A Clangutang puts extreme care into the well-being of its weapon.

Junipyro.Desc: During the summer months, Junipyro make their appearance in swarms. They are highly mischievous in nature, and sometimes accidentally set things on fire when they play. The bright red berries a Junipyro is adorned with are rumored to be delicious.

Vuliable.Desc: The most common form that a Flaskit becomes. The gas it emits is harmless. It radiates an aura of calm, and has shed its reactive nature.

Pandishi.Desc: It's rarely seen, even by the locals who tell tales of it. Sometimes, it will make an appearance to share delicious food, only to vanish once again.

Indigoo.Desc: Its body is largely incomplete, both externally and internally, leaving it with a severe lack of intelligence and ability. To combat this, it consumes as much sugar as it can find to complete itself.

Yagoat.Desc: It favors headbutting anything it can reach. When it charges, it lets out a piercing cry.

Klydaskunk.Desc: Klydaskunk come in a wide array of bright colors, leading some to believe no two are exactly alike. Despite their beauty, they are vicious by nature.

Marigrimm.Desc: An even larger and beastly looking Wydling. The status of what is under their hood is heavily disputed, and explanations teeter between human and something far more sinister. Watch out before they start to sing!

Gummelia.Desc: Its diet consists purely of candies and other sugars, making it an avid predator of Calamander. It feeds upon these sweets to complete its body and continue its growth. Even though it has wings, it cannot fly.

Roscoon.Desc: It elects to ignore most things around it, and is sensitive to loud noise. Roscoon is thoroughly protected by its defensive bundle of leaves and petals.

Rosebug.Desc: It has a voracious appetite. A newly born cluster of Rosebug has the ability to devastate a forest's foliage and trees.

Muttish.Desc: Muttish are drawn to light sources. Groups can be found gathered near particularly bright lights. Unfortunately, this will often end badly.

Spiraryu.Desc: The result of a Kowosu feeling weak and wanting to be stronger, at any cost. Spiraryu enjoy brutally crushing weaker foes with their seemingly random movements and incredible strength.

Kowosu.Desc: Kowosu are relatively weak and small, but have an iron-will and an urge to fight. They wander the wilderness searching for strong opponents and overcoming any obstacles in their path.

Runewt.Desc: A Runewt never truly stops growing, capable of reaching astounding heights decades down the line. At first glance, a resting group can be mistaken for old archeological ruins. The brightness of its markings tells of how much power an individual possesses.

Shelldo.Desc: Shelldo tend to be a menace right in the egg itself. They hatch by slamming their tails on the sides of their eggs, and continue to utilise the shells as cover or defense.

Impling.Desc: An Impling is rumored to be born when a flame is extinguished in the underworld. Energetic and childish, they are known to pull pranks on travelers.

Kitsen.Desc: Sometimes, when people get lost in the forest, a mysterious blue glow shows them the way out. This glow comes from the fox-fire of a Kitsen.

Medikrow.Desc: In the past, Medikrow were trusted to be as good as any human doctor. There was once a Medikrow who abused this trust to poison patients, and now Medikrow are seen as shady doctors who are not to be trusted.

Sharpup.Desc: Nave and curious by nature. Often drawn to the shiny hooks of fishermen, few Sharpup actually make it to evolution.

Springling.Desc: It's capable of leaping high into the air with the aid of its long, slender legs. It often perches on low tree branches, scouting and listening for danger.

Wolfreeze.Desc: Wild Wolfreeze will rarely be seen with each other. They are often the leaders of their own packs, followed by Furzen and Pupskey. Their fangs are capable of freezing anything they bite.

Kidere.Desc: Its powers of light are almost too powerful to handle, rendering a Kidere into an emotionless force of destruction. It uses polished shards of ice like mirrors to amplify and reflect its abilities, searing any who dare test its wrath.

Shyce.Desc: A Shyce is extremely shy, often found hiding behind a snowflake of its own creation. Should the snowflake be lost or disappear, it will cry until its tears form a new one.

Meltimaw.Desc: The cheese that oozes off of it is burning hot to the touch, to the point of steaming. It's unknown if the mouth that is its tail possesses any intelligence.

Squelly.Desc: It drifts peacefully through water, guided mostly by instinct and its psychic power. It always seems to be sleeping, even on the move.

Glummish.Desc: Glummish shed spores that are known to cause feelings of sadness and melancholy. A Glummish itself is hardly cheerful.

Slibble.Desc: The shell adorning its head acts as a protective barrier against damage to its brain, contained within. It has miraculous problem-solving abilities, and typically takes on an unusual approach to its solutions.

Muncheez.Desc: It has an affinity for biting things, but not to worry: it has no teeth, and is unlikely to cause harm.

Shadark.Desc: It learns through its mischievous pranks and maneuvers. It lurks in the shadows, and takes glee in leaping out and scaring anyone passing by.

Webennae.Desc: A protective wrapping made of a unique silk encases its body. It can easily absorb most physical attacks.

Caramellow.Desc: In spite of its Beast typing that is attributed to savagery, a Carshellow is gleeful and kind. It opts to envelop its company in its warm, albeit sticky hugs.

Djinneko.Desc: It's believed that a Djinneko can grant the wishes of anyone who begs it. Beware, however; it is only an illusion.

Plipo.Desc: Plipo tend to have a very hard time getting out of their eggs due to sheer mass. A Plipo will wander around for seemingly no reason until they somehow manage to evolve. This tends to come under speculation, and to this day researchers are confounded on how Plipo have managed to survive for however long they have.

Larvennae.Desc: It sticks to hiding in shady, damp areas, such as rotting logs or the roots of a tree. It's sensitive to sound vibrations, and will flee should others be nearby.

Kelpie.Desc: It resides in dim, watery areas such as swamps or coves. Each strand of its kelp-like hair is prehensile in nature.

Cocosquid.Desc: It resides inside the hollow shell of a coconut. If this coconut is destroyed, it will be devastated.

Skadean.Desc: When a Schiwi gets too big to fit into her bucket, she turns into a Skadean. Gaining confidence, she isn't afraid of the ocean any more and sets out to find her long lost family.

Levilen.Desc: Levilen are highly energetic, often making their tamers to chase after them when they run off, a game that they favor greatly. Their coarse fur charges static electricity easily.

Aspark.Desc: It's playful in nature. When riled up or excited, its thick, rough coat will stand on end, a sign that it's full of charged electricity.

Calamander.Desc: It's made entirely out of candy. Due to its small size and lack of basic survival instinct, it's frequently preyed upon. Many believe that without the aid of DoodleCo, its species would not continue to exist.

Glimmew.Desc: Glimmew use their sensitive glowing whiskers to show how they feel. If your Glimmew shines brightly, it's very happy!

Elektiel.Desc: Always tired and lethargic, Elektiel can be found lounging or sleeping near areas or buildings with high amounts of electricity, their primary source of energy.

Exovul.Desc: The result of a Flaskit that was exposed to a reactive substance. Its body is scalding hot to the touch. It's also very energetic and affectionate.

Chronos.Desc: Chronos comes from a long-forgotten species that weaves together the fabric of space-time, fixing temporal paradoxes. Chronos lead a rebellion against its former masters, creating this timeline.

Maskomedy.Desc: It's unusually cheerful, and is prone to laughter, even when the situation deems it inappropriate. It does its best to ensure others laugh just as much.

Lilbulb.Desc: Lilbulb like to lazily float around in deep waters. Their glowing heads serve as a guide for many creatures in the depths of Doodle World.

Cryotera.Desc: It lurks deep within caves, driving out others that live there and filling it with ice. Cryotera that live near settlements are often referred to as a local menace.

Coalt.Desc: For their rather small size, Coalt are quite strong, and are capable of pulling weights much heavier than their own. Nothing makes them happier than running around and building up their strength.

Crystik.Desc: It has no grace, often tripping and falling, which can be attributed to its overall poor eyesight. Crystik are often shy and cowardly.

Bionotic.Desc: It's capable of swimming even through air. It's suspected that many past UFO sightings may have just been Bionotic, as it has a unique, almost hypnotic bioluminescence in the dark.

Spunny.Desc: A forlorn-looking rabbit Doodle who was left to sit and rot in the dust. It seeks the one who abandoned it, a quest for eternal vengeance.

Prickles.Desc: Its sharp thorns and powerful arms give it an unwavering sense of self-confidence. It stops to flex frequently.

Needling.Desc: Found hopping around hot climates, it often gathers in groups of its own to regulate its body temperature, which averages at 70-80 degrees Fahrenheit.

Swoptar.Desc: It sharpens its massive claws by scoring them against rough surfaces such as trees or stone. The marks left behind also double as territory markers. Although Swoptar are typically solitary, it's not unheard of for them to live in packs of two or three.

Corrolizard.Desc: Corrolizard are very intelligent. Touching it is ill-advised; its skin can secrete a substance that is among the most deadly toxins in the world.

Grimeleon.Desc: The poison that's secreted from Grimeleons skin is relatively harmless, but heed caution to its potent, venomous bite.

Antenaflight.Desc: Due to the odd placement of its wings, it can only fly in short bursts. It uses its claws to cling to trees and branches.

Leazar.Desc: Utilizing the peculiar sprout-like protrusion from its head, a Leazar will attempt to lure prey from their hiding spots.

Tulenna.Desc: It tricks foes into attacking its tail by flicking it around in an alluring way. Then, it sprays it with spores, and flees.

Amphipyre.Desc: The flames it creates can reach upwards of several hundred degrees. The pouches on its cheeks are burning hot to the touch.

Fruitoad.Desc: A Fruitoad's scent tends to mature over time, similar to the fruit it is assumed to have evolved from. For this reason, Fruitoad are sought after companions and a symbol of wealth to own.

Thornet.Desc: It attacks by quickly and repeatedly jabbing its opponent with its sharp, barbed stinger. A group can easily become aggravated and hostile.

Nibblen.Desc: Its powerful mandibles are capable of digging into tree bark to hold it in place when storms roll through, so that it won't blow away.

Grimsugar.Desc: It lingers near populated areas in spite of its skittishness, seeking out sweets and handouts. Once it acquires a candy of its own, it sheds its nervous nature and becomes friendly.

Groato.Desc: The primary action a Groato does throughout the day is to lay around in sunny areas. Groato are also quite fond of affection, and enjoy being petted and patted by both Doodles and humans.
